  "body": "# Problem\r\n\r\nBasically account, created with keycard after unpairing card is useless - so after logout you can't login again on the same device (you can't pair it again before app reinstall)\r\nAlso If you tap back right after unpairing, you can see error:\r\n![photo_2019-10-15 14 12 11](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/4557972/66830506-ec772280-ef55-11e9-856a-6c12b135b94d.jpeg)\r\n\r\n[Status.log](https://github.com/status-im/status-react/files/3729130/Status.log)\r\n\r\nNow currently this popup is shown before unpairing:\r\n![photo_2019-10-15 14 14 20](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/4557972/66830591-192b3a00-ef56-11e9-8b6e-a948efbc052c.jpeg)\r\n\r\nSo to prevent issue with invalid account (I think we don't have option now to remove account from status) I suggest:\r\n- add more details to popup where will be clearly stated what is unpair and that you can't use this account on this device anymore unless you reinstall the app\r\n- automatic logout (with additional confirmation dialog)\r\n\r\n@andmironov @hesterbruikman would like to have your opinion on this\r\n\r\n\r\n",
